@node intr Introduction
With the advent of the new translator.library v42 there appeared a bug
in the Speak-Handler. The international characters above 127 were removed
by the old Speak-Handler. In the documentation for his spanish accent
,mr Juan Carlos Pérez Walls, mentions this bug. I then decided to make
a new Speak-Handler and fix this bug.

Speak-Handler 38.1 is hereby released as Freeware to the Amiga community.
@endnode



@node requ Requirements
Speak-Handler 38.1 requires AmigaOS 3.0+ due to the mountlist entries.

The previous version (38.0) only required 1.3 but I dropped this for two
reasons. Exec v36 has better support for device functions (CreateIORequest etc)
which makes it easier, smaller and better to write it in assembly language
(The only language there should be ;-). The second reason is the better
mountlist system in 3.0
It should be no problem to require OS 3.0 though as this release of the
Amiga OS is possible to install on any Amiga. So users that still has old
versions of the OS buy 3.1!
@endnode



@node inst Installation
The handler itself should be copied from SpeakHandler/L/Speak-Handler to
L:Speak-Handler.

If SPEAK: should be mounted automatically with every reboot:
Copy the mountlist from SpeakHandler/Storage/DOSDrivers/SPEAK#?
to DEVS:DOSDrivers.

If SPEAK: should be mounted manually:
Copy the mountlist from SpeakHandler/Storage/DOSDrivers/SPEAK#?
to SYS:Storage/DOSDrivers. Mount it with "mount SPEAK:"

I plan to write an installer script.
@endnode



@node usag Usage
When the Speak-Handler is mounted it can be accessed from shell with
the name SPEAK: Simply handle this as any other device. It can also
be used when programming by opening SPEAK: as a file and then writing
text to it.

Examples from shell:
echo "Hello!" >SPEAK:
copy "Strindberg.TXT" SPEAK:
@endnode


@node hist History
MIN	Minor bug fix
MAJ	Major bug fix
NEW	New feature
CH	Change in operation
OPT	Optimization of old feature

38.0	980728	The first release of the new Speak-Handler, which
		replaces the old Commodore Speak-Handler.
	MAJ	The bug with the filtered ascii codes above 127, as reported
		by Juan Carlos Pérez Walls, is fixed.
38.1	981107	Aminet release
	OPT	The code is 1328 bytes smaller due to assembly language
		rewriting. If all programmers wrote in assembly language
		the Amiga operating system would be much faster and even
		less hardware demanding. So all coders out there switch
		slow and memory demanding C code for assembly language!
@endnode


